# To get started

Install dependencies

    $ npm install

Start mongodb

    $ sudo service mongod start

Populate database

    $ grunt populate

Start a watch on hbs files

    $ grunt watch

Start app

    $ npm start

The app should appear at localhost:3000

To run api tests (requires server)

    $ npm run itest

# Known issues

* Can't run watch and default task in the same process
* When grunt watch task is run, there will always be an error message. The task still works though.